🎧 PodcastApp

A clean, responsive podcast browsing app built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (no frameworks required).

Users can explore a grid of podcasts, filter by genre, sort by popularity or recency, search by keyword, and view detailed show info in a modal dialog.

✨ Features

Landing Grid: Browse podcast previews in a responsive card grid.

Podcast Preview Cards: Each card shows:

Cover image

Title

Season count

Genre tags

Last updated date (human-friendly format)

Filters & Search:

Filter podcasts by genre

Sort by Recently Updated, Most Popular, or Newest

Search by title or genre

Modal Details:

Podcast cover, title, description, genres

Full last-updated date

List of seasons with episode counts

Close modal with X button, Escape key, or backdrop click

Responsive Design: Works smoothly on desktop, tablet, and mobile.

Accessibility:

Keyboard navigation (cards open modal on Enter, Escape closes modal)

Proper ARIA roles/labels

Focus management for modals

Clean Codebase:

Modular, reusable functions

Documented with JSDoc

Consistent formatting across HTML, CSS, and JS

📂 Project Structure
PodcastApp/
│
├── index.html      # Main entry point
├── styles.css      # Stylesheet (responsive grid, cards, modal, etc.)
├── script.js       # App logic (filters, rendering, modal, search)
└── README.md       # Project documentation

🚀 Getting Started

This project requires no installation. Just open the index.html file in any modern web browser.

Steps

Clone or download this repository.

Place all files (index.html, styles.css, script.js, README.md) in the same folder.

Open index.html in Chrome, Firefox, or Edge.

Start browsing podcasts 🎉

🛠️ Technologies

HTML5 – semantic structure

CSS3 – modern layout with Grid & Flexbox, responsive design

Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+) – rendering, filtering, sorting, modal logic

JSDoc – inline code documentation

